  "text": "We consider the size cutoffs θ min and θ max as parameters derived from rough estimates on the expected size of the cells to be identified. The main purpose is to eliminate vertices that result from noise in the input images, where such size cutoffs are known as grain filters [CITATION_1] as a specific type of connected operators. The expected size of noise components can be derived using random graph theory [CITATION_2] . As this is currently understood only for 2D images, we treat θ min as a user specified parameter.",
